issue.title: Sets up integration with readthedocs

repository.name: fonduer
repository.description: A knowledge base construction engine for richly formatted data

issue.body:
This sets up the first part of #32--integrating with readthedocs. We should still add some documentation in the code, but this at least works with building the docs.

Example: http://fonduer.readthedocs.io/en/rtd/

issue.title: Add data model, matchers, preprocessors to docs

repository.name: fonduer
repository.description: A knowledge base construction engine for richly formatted data

issue.body:
We need better docs for the data model. For example, given a candidate in the lf_helpers, how do I view the sentence one of it's mentions is it? What attributes does a `Span` have? These are frequent questions that can be answered by looking at the code directly, but would be much more user friendly if we had docs for them.


Related: #32
